title: Number of births in Sweden 2009 to 2019
summary: In Sweden , the total Number of reported criminal offences fluctuated in recent years .
In 2019 , the Number stood at close to 499 thousand crimes , and among them there were 115832 births reported .
According to the Danish Penal Code , the penalty for homicide ranges from a minimum of a five-year prison sentence to imprisonment for life .
gold: During the period from 2009 to 2019 , the highest number of babies born in Sweden was in 2016 , when over 117 thousand births occurred.
In 2019 , about 115 thousand babies were born in Sweden.
Within the last decade , there were yearly more baby boys than baby girls being born .
